
/*
 * // This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to modify node values using the [set-value] slot and concatenate strings using the [strings.concat] slot. The code sets the value of the [.handle] node to true and appends the string "SASS file" to the current value of the [.file-meta] node. Below is a detailed explanation of each slot used in the code.
 * // 1. [case] - This is the root node, which might be part of a larger conditional or switch statement.
 * // 2. [set-value] - Changes the value of the [.handle] node to true.
 * // 3. [strings.concat] - Concatenates the current value of the [.file-meta] node with the string "SASS file".
 * // 4. [get-value] - Retrieves the current value of the [.file-meta] node to be used in the concatenation process.
 */
case:sass
   set-value:x:@.handle
      .:bool:true
   set-value:x:@.file-meta
      strings.concat
         get-value:x:@.file-meta
         .:SASS file
